Overall Layout
Page Title — "Transactions" in large bold dark green text at the top left.
Top Bar — Shows current time/date, notification bell (5 badges), and admin avatar "AD" on the top right.
Sidebar — Same dark green navigation as the dashboard; "Transactions" is currently the active/highlighted page.

Transaction Type Filter Tabs
Renew — Yellow/gold outlined tab; filters the table to show only renewal transactions.
Redeem — Green outlined tab; filters for redeemed pawn contracts.
New Pawn — Dark green outlined tab; filters for newly created pawn transactions.
Sales / Transfer — Purple filled/active tab; filters for sold items or buyer transfers.
Buy Back — Blue outlined tab; filters for buy-back transactions from customers.
Export CSV — Top right button; exports the current transaction table data as a CSV file for external use.
Print Report — Top right green button; sends the current table view to print for physical records.

Summary Metric Cards
Pawned Today — 28 — Total number of pawn transactions created today; tagged as "Active contracts" in green.
Buy Back — 12 — Number of buy-back transactions completed today; tagged as "Purchased today" in blue.
Renewed — 8 — Number of contracts renewed today; tagged as "Contracts Renewed" in yellow/orange.
Sold Item — 28 — Number of inventory items sold today; tagged as "Units sold" in red/orange.
Branch Balance — 12 — Current cash on hand for the branch; tagged as "Current cash" in dark/neutral color.

⚠️ Revised: Branch Balance Card (from meeting)
Starting Balance — A new field to be added showing the cash balance at the start of the day (set automatically from the previous day's ending balance).
Ending Balance — A new field showing the running total after all cash-ins and cash-outs for the day.
Logic — Ending balance today automatically becomes the starting balance tomorrow.
Daily Reset — System resets at 12:00 AM; the ending balance carries over as the next day's starting balance before resetting transaction counts.

Daily Transactions Table
Transaction # — Unique system-generated ID per transaction (e.g., SJS007610, SJS007611). The first row "SJS007610" is highlighted in dark green as the starting/opening entry.
Purpose — Color-coded badge showing the transaction type: Buy Back (blue), Renew (green), Pawn (purple), Sold Item (orange/red), Start (gray).
Date — Date the transaction was recorded (e.g., 4/1/2026).
Time — Exact time the transaction was logged (e.g., 8:21 AM, 9:39 AM).
Cash In — Amount of cash received in that transaction. Currently shows fixed values; revision requires this to be manually editable with a text input so the user can type custom details and source.
Cash Out — Amount of cash paid out in that transaction; deducted from the branch balance automatically.
Return — Return amount if applicable to the transaction.
Unit — Name/description of the item involved (e.g., iPhone, Oppo Reno, Xiaomi R...).
Unit Code — Internal inventory code assigned to the item (e.g., 10-JCLB-11529).
Pawn — Pawn amount associated with the transaction (e.g., 1000, 1700); highlighted in bold purple.
Storage — Storage fee charged if applicable (e.g., 400, 120); shown in bold purple.

⚠️ Revised: Cash In / Cash Out Logic (from meeting)
Editable Cash In — Cash In should no longer be a fixed/automatic field. The user (branch admin/manager) can manually type the amount and details (e.g., "Cash from management," "Sales revenue," etc.).
Cash In adds to Branch Balance — Every Cash In entry increases the current branch balance automatically.
Cash Out deducts from Branch Balance — Every Cash Out entry reduces the branch balance in real time.
Starting Balance Row — A dedicated row or card to show the opening cash at the start of the day.
Ending Balance Row — A running total that updates as transactions are added throughout the day.
Carry-Over Logic — At 12:00 AM reset, the ending balance of the current day is saved and automatically set as the starting balance for the next day.

Super Admin vs. Branch Manager View
Super Admin — Can view this same Transactions page for all branches; branch selector dropdown would be available to switch between branches or view all combined.
Branch Manager — Sees the exact same design and layout but transactions are scoped only to their assigned branch; no branch switcher available.
